article.headline: Mercer 74, Stetson 73
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- James Odums scored four points in the final two seconds, including a putback as time expired, to lift Mercer to a 74-73 victory over Stetson Friday night. The Hatters (10-16, 8-11 Atlantic Sun Conference) led 71-70 when Anthony Register hit a couple of free throws with 10.9 seconds remaining. But Odums was fouled and went to the line for three attempts. After making the first two shots, Odums rebounded his missed shot and hit the game-winning jumper for the Bears (15-11, 10-9). Will Emerson, who finished with a career-high 29 points, scored 12 straight points to give Mercer a 68-67 lead. Jacob Skogen, who went 6-for-9 from beyond the arc, had 18 points. Register led Stetson with 23 points and Borislav Djordjic had 18. E.J. Gordon added 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds.
